<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Closure on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/closure/</link><description>Recent content in Closure on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/closure/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ Lambda Capture — Lambda Capture Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/lambda-capture/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/lambda-capture/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-lambda-capture--lambda-capture-error-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ Lambda Capture — Lambda Capture Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lambda capture errors occur when a lambda captures a variable by reference and the variable goes out of scope before the lambda is invoked, when a needed variable is not captured, or when moving captured values incorrectly. These lead to undefined behavior or compilation errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-lambda-capture-errors-occur"&gt;Why Lambda Capture Errors Occur&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include capturing local variables by reference that go out of scope, forgetting to capture &lt;code&gt;this&lt;/code&gt; in member lambdas, accidentally capturing by value when mutation is needed, and using &lt;code&gt;[=]&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;[&amp;amp;]&lt;/code&gt; over-capturing unintended variables.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Groovy Closure Wrong Number of Arguments</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/groovy-closureerror-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/groovy-closureerror-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A closure error occurs when a Groovy closure is called with a different number of arguments than it expects. Groovy closures can accept variable arguments but must be defined appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closure expects 1 argument but called with 0&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closure expects 0 arguments but called with 1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Method closure signature mismatch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using wrong closure call syntax&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Closure expects 1 arg, called with 0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; greet &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, $name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: Expected 1 arg, got 0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use default or zero-arg closure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; greet &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;World&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, $name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// &amp;#34;Hello, World&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Closure expects 0 args, called with 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; sayHello &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sayHello&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: Expected 0 args, got 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Accept variable args
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; sayHello &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, ${name ?: &amp;#39;World&amp;#39;}!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sayHello&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// &amp;#34;Hello, Alice!&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: forEach closure signature
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;].&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;each&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; it&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; index &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong signature for each
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;$it at $index&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: each() only provides value, use eachWithIndex
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;].&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;eachWithIndex&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; val&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; index &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; println &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;$val at $index&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Variable argument closure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; process &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; Object&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt; args &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; args&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;each&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; println it &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;process&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;])&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Closure with optional param
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; greet &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; String name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;World&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, $name!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// &amp;#34;Hello, World!&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// &amp;#34;Hello, Alice!&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: Method closure with correct arity
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Calculator&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; add &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; a&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; negate &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;it &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; calc &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Calculator&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;println calc&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// 5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;println calc&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;negate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// -5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=""&gt;groovy-missingmethod&lt;/a&gt; — missing method&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/groovy-missingproperty/"&gt;groovy-missingproperty&lt;/a&gt; — missing property&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/groovy-nullpointererror/"&gt;groovy-nullpointererror&lt;/a&gt; — null pointer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PHP First Class Callable: Syntax Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/php-first-class-callable-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/php-first-class-callable-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="php-first-class-callable-syntax-error-fix"&gt;PHP First Class Callable: Syntax Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A PHP first class callable error occurs when you use incorrect syntax for creating first class callables. This feature was introduced in PHP 8.1.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PHP 8.1 introduced first class callable syntax using &lt;code&gt;Closure::fromCallable()&lt;/code&gt; or the short syntax &lt;code&gt;strlen(...)&lt;/code&gt;. This allows passing a function as a callable without wrapping it in a closure. Errors occur when the syntax is wrong or the function doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Closure error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/closure-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/closure-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Closure error occurs when a closure is called with incorrect arguments, when the closure itself throws an exception, or when there&amp;rsquo;s a mismatch between the expected and actual closure signature.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong number of arguments passed to closure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closure accessing undeclared variables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closure throwing an exception&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing return statement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Wrong number of arguments
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; add &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; a&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;add&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// closure expects 2 arguments
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Provide correct arguments
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; add &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; a&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;add&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Closure with undeclared variable
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; process &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; it&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// &amp;#39;it&amp;#39; is implicit
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;process&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// no argument provided
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Define parameters explicitly
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; process &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; item &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; item&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;value&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;process&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;([&lt;/span&gt;value: &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;])&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Wrong arity
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; greet &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, $name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// MissingMethodException (wrong number of args)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Exception inside closure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; risky &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; RuntimeException&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;oops&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;risky&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// RuntimeException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: Closure returning null
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; find &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; list &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; list&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;find&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; it &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; find&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;([&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;])&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// result is null, may cause NPE later
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/null-pointer5"&gt;NullPointerException&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/missing-method"&gt;MissingMethodException: No signature of method&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Closure error in Groovy</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/groovy-closureerror/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/groovy-closureerror/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closures in Groovy are blocks of code that can be passed around and executed later. Errors occur due to scoping issues, delegate resolution, or incorrect parameter binding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Variable not in closure&amp;rsquo;s lexical scope&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delegate method not found&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Closure called with wrong number of arguments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;it&lt;/code&gt; keyword ambiguity with multiple parameters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Variable not in scope
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; closure &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; println x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;closure&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// x not defined
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Define x before the closure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;closure&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Closure called with wrong args
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; greet &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; println &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, ${name}&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// wrong number of args
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Provide the argument
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; items &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; sum &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;items&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;each&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; sum &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; it &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;println sum &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// 6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; fn &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; a&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;fn&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// wrong number of arguments error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/missing-method"&gt;MissingMethodException&lt;/a&gt; - method not found&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/groovy/missing-property"&gt;MissingPropertyException&lt;/a&gt; - property not found&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PHP create_function() Deprecated — Use Anonymous Functions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/php/create-function/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/deprecated/php/create-function/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-php-create_function-deprecated--use-anonymous-functions"&gt;[Solution] PHP create_function() Deprecated — Use Anonymous Functions&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;create_function()&lt;/code&gt; function was deprecated in PHP 7.2 and removed in PHP 8.0. It was essentially an &lt;code&gt;eval()&lt;/code&gt; wrapper that created a named function at runtime. Modern PHP uses anonymous functions (closures) with the &lt;code&gt;function () {}&lt;/code&gt; syntax, which is cleaner, faster, and more secure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-youll-see"&gt;What You&amp;rsquo;ll See&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On PHP 7.2 through 7.4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Deprecated: create_function() is deprecated in /path/to/script.php on line X
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;On PHP 8.0+:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>